1. Install git
sudo apt-get install git

2. Configure your name
git config --global user.name "Your name"

3. Check for name
git config --global user.name

4. Configure email
git config --global user.email "email@example.com"

5. Check for mail
git config --global user.email

6. Create a new directory with name of your choice

7. cd into that directory

8. Run following commands
    - git init
    - git remote add origin  https://gitlab.com/gdadlaney/kitas.git
    - git pull origin master
    
9. After changing any file at the end of the day run following commands
    - git add .
    - git commit -m "message"
    - git pull origin master
    - git push origin master
    
    
NOTE: if on pull error like this appears
From https://gitlab.com/gdadlaney/kitas
 * branch            master     -> FETCH_HEAD
fatal: refusing to merge unrelated histories

then run following command
 git merge origin/master --allow-unrelated-histories